<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3229] unexpected Timeout exception when desired bytes are only partially available</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3229</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;TBinaryProtocolImpl.ReadMessageBegin can raise a TTransportException. This happens with big result data. TTcpSocketStreamImpl.Read will raise a &apos;Process successfully finished&apos; exception. &lt;br/&gt;
I think the problem is in TTcpSocketStreamImpl.WaitForData: retVal is bigger than DesiredBytes. Exists here a probleme with intermediate chunks?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Delphi XE6 on Windows 7&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
